The paper deals with geometric graphs and their properties, specifically the Yao graph and its spanning ratio. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also uses mathematical analysis and optimization techniques, which could place it under discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of the Yao graph, which could make it relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
